canonical:
  title: 賀箋
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 惟忠惟孝允孚上帝之心以長以賢遂正前星之位輿情攸屬邦本不搖云云德禀川冲學惇日就琱珉錫冊永觀萬國之貞靑盖乘車端奉一人之慶躬任承祧之重意專問寢之勤伏念早忝末寮優承厚睠鯷岑滯迹未預賀班鵠海馳誠難禁喜淚
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀箋
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 惟忠惟孝。允孚上帝之心。以長以賢。遂正前星之位。輿情攸屬。邦本不搖。云云。德禀川冲。學惇日就。琱珉錫冊。永觀萬國之貞。靑盖乘車。端奉一人之慶。躬任承祧之重。意專問寢之勤。伏念早忝末寮。優承厚睠。鯷岑滯迹。未預賀班。鵠海馳誠。難禁喜淚。
korean:
  title: 하전
  author: 이제현
  language: kor
  text: 오직 충성되고 오직 효도로워 진실로 상제(上帝)의 마음에 맞고, 장자(長子)이면서도 어지시므로 드디어 전성(前星)의 위(位)를 바로하시니, 여정(輿情)이 속(屬)하는 바요, 방본(邦本)이 든든해졌나이다. 운운. 덕(德)이 천충(川冲)을 품부(稟賦)하시고 학문이 날로 성취하시어, 이제 옥책(玉冊)을 내리시오니 길이 만국이 바로잡힘을 보게 되었습니다. 청개(靑蓋)의 수레를 타사 단정히 한 분의 경사를 받들고, 몸소 승조(承祚)의 중임(重任)을 맡으신 중에도 마음은 오로지 부지런히 문안(問安)을 드림에 있사옵나이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 일찍 말료(末寮)에 봉직(奉職)하였을 때 외람되이 후권(厚睠)을 입었사온데, 이제 제잠(鯷岑)에 자취가 구애되어 하반(賀班)에 참석치 못하오나, 곡해(鵠海)에 정성을 달리며 기쁜 눈물을 금치 못하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0100&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Congratulatory Memorial
  author: Lee Je-hyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Through loyalty alone, through filial piety alone, his sincerity reaches the heart of Heaven above. As the eldest yet possessed of wisdom, he has rightfully ascended to the position of the fore-star. The people's hearts turn toward him, and the realm's foundation stands firm. Thus it is.

    Virtue flows through him like a mighty river; learning ripens with each passing day. Now the jade decree descends—eternal witness to the righteousness of ten thousand nations. In his chariot beneath the azure canopy, he receives the blessing meant for one alone, while bearing upon his shoulders the weight of succession. Yet even in this station, his heart remains steadfast in the simple duty of inquiring after his father's health.

    I reflect with reverence: once, in my humble station among the minor officials, I undeservedly received your generous regard. Now, confined to my obscure corner, I cannot join the great celebration. Yet across the distance, my sincerity flies forth—and I cannot restrain the tears of joy that flow.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'fore-star' (前星) refers to the heir apparent or crown prince position, a classical reference to celestial order mirrored in political hierarchy.
  - key: ''
    value: The mention of 'inquiring after his father's health' (問寢) emphasizes Confucian filial duty, suggesting the recipient, though elevated to high office, remains devoted to parental care.
  - key: ''
    value: This appears to be a congratulatory memorial written by Lee Je-hyeon (a prominent Goryeo scholar-official) expressing his inability to attend an official celebration in person, while conveying his sincere joy from afar.
